# Order vs Reference Document Comparison — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A new feature that accepts two PDFs (an **Order** and a **Reference** document), extracts text from both, sends them to GPT-4o with a structured 8-step comparison prompt, and returns a detailed discrepancy analysis with confidence scoring and an executive report.

## Files Created

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [OrderComparator.py](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/backend/ai/OrderComparator.py) | AI engine: builds comparison prompt, calls GPT-4o, parses JSON + report |
| [order_comparison.py](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/backend/api/order_comparison.py) | FastAPI route `POST /compare/upload` with Pydantic response models |
| [OrderComparison.tsx](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/frontend/src/components/comparison/OrderComparison.tsx) | React component: dual file upload, results tables, confidence meter, risk badge |
| [test_order_comparison.py](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/backend/tests/test_order_comparison.py) | 8 unit tests with mocked LLM responses |

