## Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A["Frontend<br/>OrderComparison.tsx"] -->|"2 PDFs via FormData"| B["POST /compare/upload<br/>order_comparison.py"]
    B -->|"PyPDF2 + OCR"| C["Text Extraction"]
    C -->|"order_text + reference_text"| D["OrderComparator.py"]
    D -->|"System Prompt + Texts"| E["GPT-4o via langchain-openai"]
    E -->|"JSON + Report"| D
    D -->|"Parsed Result"| B
    B -->|"OrderComparisonResponse"| A
```

## Test Results

All 8 unit tests passed:
- [test_extract_json_from_code_block](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/backend/tests/test_order_comparison.py#103-110) — Parses JSON from ` ```json ``` ` markers
- [test_extract_json_fallback_bare_json](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/backend/tests/test_order_comparison.py#111-115) — Falls back to bare JSON
- [test_extract_json_parse_failure](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/backend/tests/test_order_comparison.py#116-120) — Returns structured error on garbage input
- [test_extract_report](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/backend/tests/test_order_comparison.py#121-126) — Extracts executive report from `EXECUTIVE_REPORT:` marker
- [test_extract_report_missing](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/backend/tests/test_order_comparison.py#127-130) — Handles missing report gracefully
- [test_compare_full_flow](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/backend/tests/test_order_comparison.py#131-149) — Full mocked LLM comparison works end-to-end
- [test_compare_malformed_response](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/backend/tests/test_order_comparison.py#150-164) — Graceful degradation for malformed LLM output
- [test_missing_api_key](file:///c:/Users/anude/Documents/GitHub/Decision-Support-System/backend/tests/test_order_comparison.py#165-175) — Raises `ValueError` when `OPENAI_API_KEY` is not set

## How to Use

1. Set `OPENAI_API_KEY` in your `.env` file
2. Start backend: `python -m uvicorn backend.main:app --reload`
3. Start frontend: `cd frontend && npm start`
4. Navigate to **Order Compare** in the nav bar
5. Upload an Order PDF and a Reference PDF → click **Compare Documents**
